{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/post/announcing-codesandbox-2-0","webpackCompilationHash":"43a07f76784e304bf1a0","result":{"data":{"blogPost":{"fields":{"authors":["Ives van Hoorne"],"date":"2017-11-16T00:00:00.000Z","description":"Git committing, a new homepage, static file hosting and more","photo":"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/587016?s=460&v=4","slug":"announcing-codesandbox-2-0","title":"Announcing CodeSandbox 2.0"},"frontmatter":{"banner":{"publicURL":"/static/banner-6b1b00cd480f5526513c3832cf75219a.png"}},"html":"<p>It has been 7 months since\n<a href=\"/post/codesandbox-an-online-react-editor\">we announced CodeSandbox</a>, and one\nyear since I made the\n<a href=\"https://github.com/codesandbox/codesandbox-client/commit/c5f43786fe6a4e54c3b7729d8992dba5a4adeeaf\">first commit</a>.\nCan you imagine? This certainly deserves a celebration, and we decided to do\nthat with a big update! I took the last 2 weeks off to work fulltime on\n<a href=\"https://codesandbox.io\">CodeSandbox</a> and we were able to get a lot done.<br>\nLet's dive in!</p>\n<section>\n<h2 id=\"new-homepage\"><a href=\"#new-homepage\" aria-label=\"new homepage permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>New Homepage</h2>\n<p>Since the first release we've added many things to CodeSandbox. To give you an\nidea: we released CodeSandbox without embeds! A lot has changed, we're not an\neditor for <a href=\"https://github.com/facebook/react\">React</a> only anymore, and I think\nwe moved past the definition of a playground. All these changes, but the\nhomepage didn't receive a single update. This caused confusion, as people didn't\nknow about the things we built. It was time to do something about that. We've\nnow designed and built the homepage from scratch using\n<a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby\">Gatsby</a>.\n<a href=\"https://codesandbox.io\">You can see it here</a>! A very big thanks to\n<a href=\"https://twitter.com/druchtie\">Danny Ruchtie</a> for helping us with the design.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/a247ca1214e9d56e4c5f12222224f7f7/0.gif\"></p>\n<p>There are more pages in the pipeline, like documentation and picked examples. We\nalso want to show a more personalized page for logged in users. The basis is\nhere now, so it'll be easier to expand to this in the future.</p>\n</section>\n<section>\n<h2 id=\"github-committing--opening-prs\"><a href=\"#github-committing--opening-prs\" aria-label=\"github committing  opening prs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>GitHub Committing &#x26; Opening PRs</h2>\n<p>The most requested feature since day one is committing to\n<a href=\"https://github.com\">GitHub</a>. At the beginning we couldn't tackle that because\nof the groundwork that needed to be built first. The groundwork has been built\nand from now on you can commit, create repositories and open pull requests right\nfrom within CodeSandbox! It truly feels incredible to commit changes directly\nfrom your browser to GitHub.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/d4485773926a52a4762932a657df1513/1.gif\"></p>\n<h4 id=\"creating-repositories\"><a href=\"#creating-repositories\" aria-label=\"creating repositories permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Creating Repositories</h4>\n<p>This is a very simple process. You can now export any normal sandbox to GitHub\nby just entering the name and clicking 'Create Repo' in the sidebar. This will\ncreate a repository and then redirect you to the Git version of the sandbox.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 524px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/55c5c763e81784c1f1064ef402fdaa32/606d7/2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 59.160305343511446%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"2\"\n        title=\"2\"\n        src=\"/static/55c5c763e81784c1f1064ef402fdaa32/606d7/2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/55c5c763e81784c1f1064ef402fdaa32/d5c4a/2.png 185w,\n/static/55c5c763e81784c1f1064ef402fdaa32/04e89/2.png 370w,\n/static/55c5c763e81784c1f1064ef402fdaa32/606d7/2.png 524w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 524px) 100vw, 524px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h4 id=\"committing--opening-prs\"><a href=\"#committing--opening-prs\" aria-label=\"committing  opening prs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Committing &#x26; Opening PRs</h4>\n<p>To commit to your repository you'll need to import it first. You can import any\nGitHub repository by appending the GitHub URL to <code class=\"language-text\">codesandbox.io/s/github</code>. For\nexample, for my test repository the url would be:\n<a href=\"https://codesandbox.io/s/github/CompuIves/codesandbox-test-git-app\">codesandbox.io/s/github/CompuIves/codesandbox-test-git-app</a>.\nThe next step is to create a fork of this sandbox and make your changes, from\nthen on you can commit or open a PR, by clicking on the buttons in the sidebar.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 722px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b68205e34daab2d0b8e1ed4f18361b6b/fef0a/3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 73.9612188365651%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Create a commit or open a PR\"\n        title=\"Create a commit or open a PR\"\n        src=\"/static/b68205e34daab2d0b8e1ed4f18361b6b/fef0a/3.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b68205e34daab2d0b8e1ed4f18361b6b/d5c4a/3.png 185w,\n/static/b68205e34daab2d0b8e1ed4f18361b6b/04e89/3.png 370w,\n/static/b68205e34daab2d0b8e1ed4f18361b6b/fef0a/3.png 722w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 722px) 100vw, 722px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>We first try to make a commit, if this fails we try to make a merge commit. When\na merge commit fails as well we fall back to opening a Pull Request. Merge\nconflict solving is next on our list to build inside CodeSandbox.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/4a655c1ee08e8ba5c690b5b976848036/4.gif\" alt=\"Committing some changes 😃\"></p>\n<p>You can only commit to repositories you have write access to, you can open a PR\nto any repository.</p>\n<h4 id=\"other-changes\"><a href=\"#other-changes\" aria-label=\"other changes permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Other Changes</h4>\n<p>To properly support GitHub in CodeSandbox we had to make some changes. We now\nimport all files (like <code class=\"language-text\">.gitignore</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">package.json</code>) for git repositories. We\nalso implemented custom 'editors' for binary files, like images. This feels\ngreat for me, because you now work on your project in CodeSandbox as if you are\nworking locally. There is no transforming happening anymore. The next feature\nalso helps with that.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 740px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/23095d7dfe08fd6ca8930f5e3e0e5685/0309e/5.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 54.6875%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"An Image view\"\n        title=\"An Image view\"\n        src=\"/static/23095d7dfe08fd6ca8930f5e3e0e5685/bcf2d/5.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/23095d7dfe08fd6ca8930f5e3e0e5685/d5c4a/5.png 185w,\n/static/23095d7dfe08fd6ca8930f5e3e0e5685/04e89/5.png 370w,\n/static/23095d7dfe08fd6ca8930f5e3e0e5685/bcf2d/5.png 740w,\n/static/23095d7dfe08fd6ca8930f5e3e0e5685/dbb75/5.png 1110w,\n/static/23095d7dfe08fd6ca8930f5e3e0e5685/0309e/5.png 1280w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n</section>\n<section>\n<h2 id=\"static-file-hosting\"><a href=\"#static-file-hosting\" aria-label=\"static file hosting permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Static File Hosting</h2>\n<p>One of the biggest differences between the local development server and\nCodeSandbox was the behaviour of <code class=\"language-text\">index.html</code> and the <code class=\"language-text\">public</code> folder.\nCodeSandbox didn't host the files in the <code class=\"language-text\">public</code> folder, which was confusing\nuntil now. From this update on we do host all files from the <code class=\"language-text\">public</code> (or\n<code class=\"language-text\">static</code> for <a href=\"https://github.com/vuejs/vue\">Vue</a>) directory. Many exciting\npossibilities arise with this. You can, for example, add\n<a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Workers_API\">Web Workers</a>,\nstatic images, mock API call responses now. You also get full control of\n<code class=\"language-text\">index.html</code> from now on!</p>\n<p>Here is an example sandbox:</p>\n<p><iframe src=\"https://codesandbox.io/embed/wkzowlw747?fontsize=14&view=split\" style=\"width:100%; height:500px; border:0; border-radius: 4px; overflow:hidden;\"></iframe></p>\n<!-- We download test.json from the public folder -->\n</section>\n<section>\n<h2 id=\"future\"><a href=\"#future\" aria-label=\"future permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Future</h2>\n<p>This new update adds many advanced features, and also opened up many new things\nto build. I'm looking forward to work on these points in the very near future\n(along with the existing features that are planned).</p>\n<h4 id=\"ui-overhaul\"><a href=\"#ui-overhaul\" aria-label=\"ui overhaul permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>UI Overhaul</h4>\n<p>The UI is getting a bit cluttered, and deserves some reorganization. I'm working\non a UI overhaul that I couldn't fit in this update, but certainly want to\ndeploy very soon. The new UI is inspired by\n<a href=\"https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode\">VS Code</a> and will put all advanced\nfeatures like deployment and GitHub support in their own place.</p>\n<h4 id=\"diff-view\"><a href=\"#diff-view\" aria-label=\"diff view permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Diff View</h4>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://github.com/git/git\">Git</a> integration is currently missing a diff\nview for commits. This is very important and on the top of my list to tackle.\nThis change will go together with the UI Overhaul.</p>\n<h4 id=\"configuration-source-of-truth\"><a href=\"#configuration-source-of-truth\" aria-label=\"configuration source of truth permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Configuration Source of Truth</h4>\n<p>Now that we import files like <code class=\"language-text\">package.json</code> we need to do some conflict\nresolving between CodeSandbox configs and file configs. We want to make files\nlike <code class=\"language-text\">package.json</code> the\n<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Single_source_of_truth\">source of truth</a> for eg.\ndependencies, and show a UI to configure these files. This gives the user\nflexibility and we still keep the UX very user friendly.</p>\n</section>\n<section>\n<h2 id=\"conclusion\"><a href=\"#conclusion\" aria-label=\"conclusion permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>The past 7 months were great, developing CodeSandbox has been fun from the start\nto now. One thing we didn't expect is the amount of support we received when we\nwent open source. The open source community is truly amazing and all our\ncontributors deserve one extra big thanks.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 740px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b8907b464ae149aad4ba79ef5316843d/b241b/6.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 64.1891891891892%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"6\"\n        title=\"6\"\n        src=\"/static/b8907b464ae149aad4ba79ef5316843d/bcf2d/6.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b8907b464ae149aad4ba79ef5316843d/d5c4a/6.png 185w,\n/static/b8907b464ae149aad4ba79ef5316843d/04e89/6.png 370w,\n/static/b8907b464ae149aad4ba79ef5316843d/bcf2d/6.png 740w,\n/static/b8907b464ae149aad4ba79ef5316843d/b241b/6.png 888w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>If you like what we're doing, consider becoming a\n<a href=\"https://codesandbox.io/patron\">Patron</a>. The last 2 weeks were amazing, and I'd\nlove to work more fulltime on CodeSandbox. But this is only possible if I'm able\nto afford my food 😃.</p>\n</section>"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"id":"d43e28a8-d371-531f-bd62-8858e0d75204"}}}